This house has been on my mood board for so many different projects. For some reason I always find my way back to it. And always have it as a constant source of inspiration. 

So I was so thrilled that I managed to get to see it on the last leg of my trip in Mexico City. 
 
This private residence was built in 1976-78 by Luis Barragan and was his final work.  It is truly far more breathtaking in person than my pictures could ever show.

It’s reservation only to view so definitely plan ahead on your next trip to Mexico City. 

#mexicocity #luisbarragan #casagilardi #interiordesign #architecture #mexicandesign #mexicanarchitecture

One thing I tell designers looking for advice is get used to the word ‘no’. The key to rejection is not internalizing it as a failure. I heard the word ‘no’ so many times when I first started out, but I was very clear on executing my vision and kept persisting until it turned into a yes. 

You need to remember: a ‘no’ may lead you to a yes that is even better than you planned ❤️

#fashiondesigner #designer #fashionbrand #businesstips #CUSHNIE

Hiring staff when you’re first starting out your fashion brand can be tricky. My biggest advice: take stock of your gaps and fill them in with people who are willing to wear a lot of hats and understand your vision. 

#fashiondesigner #fashionbrand #designer #businessadvice #CUSHNIE

When you’re early in your career it’s easy to just jump at any opportunity you get. The opportunity I was offered at Oscar de la Renta was incredible but I was clear in the path I wanted to take. When your vision for your career is set, you’re able to make decisions about your next steps with clarity.

When you’re running a business you are the HR department. It can be tricky to manage a team filled with different communication styles and personalities, all while making sure everything is done right and on time. Setting the company culture from the start is crucial. You need to realize you’re going to have to lead some hard conversations, but being clear and honest will help to build respect and loyalty from your team.

If you’re a creative trying to build a business you must take time to be creative! I know this sounds like such a simple concept but it’s one that I (and many people) often neglect. 

One of the biggest mistakes I made as I was building my fashion brand was getting stuck in the day-to-day grind and neglecting what got me there in the first place: my creativity. 

So as soon as I got stuck or felt depleted I began to schedule time off to spend with just myself to go to an exhibition, art show or concert. I always produced my best work when I was nurturing my creativity outside of fashion. 

Let me know if you resonate with this ❤️
